@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Mindlift</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            color: #333;
        }

        .privacy-container {
            max-width: 800px;
            width: 100%;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border-top: 6px solid #0073e6;
            margin: 50px auto;
        }

        .terms-section h2 {
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            color: #005bb5;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #e0e0e0;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }

        .terms-section p {
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            margin: 15px 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Navbar or other sections can go here and will not be affected by the privacy policy styles -->

    <div class="privacy-container">
        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2>1. Information Collection</h2>
            <p>We collect various types of personal information when you sign up, use our services, or interact with our website. This may include your name, email address, demographic information, IP address, and content you review or interact with.</p>

            <h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to improve our services, enhance user experience, provide relevant content, analyze site performance, and communicate with users. We may also use this information to prevent fraud, enforce our terms, and comply with legal obligations.</p>

            <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We respect your privacy and do not sell or share your data with third-party companies, except in cases where it is required by law, to protect our rights, or as part of a merger or acquisition.</p>

            <h2>4. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p>Our website uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect and analyze information about your use of our site. This helps us understand how users interact with our content and improve functionality. You can adjust your browser settings to refuse cookies, but this may affect your experience on our site.</p>

            <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement a variety of security measures to safeguard your personal information. However, no online platform can guarantee absolute security. By using our site, you acknowledge and accept these inherent security risks.</p>

            <h2>6. Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>Our website may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to read their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>

            <h2>7. User Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information stored with us. You can exercise these rights by contacting our support team. Please note that some information may be retained as required by law or for legitimate business purposes.</p>

            <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed about our privacy practices.</p>

            <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at support@mindlift.com.</p>
        </section>
        </section>
    </div>
</body>